HEADWORD: Liturate
<hw>Lit"u*rate</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧t"u*r⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lituratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>liturare</ets> to erase, fr.
<ets>litura</ets> a blur.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having indistinct spots, paler at their margins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Spotted, as if from abrasions of
the surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

